      <!-- TL;DR -->
      <section id="tldr" class="guide-section tldr" data-toc>
        <h2>Quick take</h2>
        <ul class="tldr-list">
          <li><strong>What it is:</strong> Supplements people use to support focus, memory, mood, or energy.</li>
          <li><strong>Who it’s for:</strong> Beginners who want simple, safe‑minded starts—no complex stacks required.</li>
          <li><strong>How to start:</strong> Use 3 steps—Base → Choline support → Goal‑specific booster.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="archetypes">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Focus</h3>
            <p>Task‑friendly clarity. Add this trio.</p>
            <a class="btn btn--sm" href="#quick-start">Show me the 3‑step plan</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Calm</h3>
            <p>Smoother attention on stress‑heavy days.</p>
            <a class="btn btn--sm" href="#quick-start">Show me the 3‑step plan</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Memory</h3>
            <p>Learning + recall that builds with consistency.</p>
            <a class="btn btn--sm" href="#quick-start">Show me the 3‑step plan</a>
          </article>
        </div>
        <div class="toggle-simplify">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="simplifyToggle"> Simplify reading</label>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT ARE NOOTROPICS -->
      <section id="what-are-nootropics" class="guide-section" data-toc>
        <h2>What are nootropics?</h2>
        <p>Nootropics are substances—often dietary supplements—that people use to support mental performance such as focus, memory, motivation, or stress resilience. They are not magic, and effects vary. They work best alongside good sleep, nutrition, and movement.</p>
        <ul class="bullets two-col">
          <li>May support attention, learning, clarity, or stress balance.</li>
          <li>Not medical treatment. Consult your clinician if you have a condition or take meds.</li>
          <li>Start low, add slowly; some items require cycling.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="glossary-chips">
          <span class="chip" title="Supports stress balance over time.">Adaptogen</span>
          <span class="chip" title="Relates to acetylcholine pathways.">Cholinergic</span>
          <span class="chip" title="A family of synthetic compounds explored for cognition.">Racetam</span>
          <span class="chip" title="The brain’s ability to adapt and rewire.">Neuroplasticity</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- HOW TO CHOOSE -->
